1
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:33,000
"Bittersweet Love"

2
00:01:33,500 --> 00:01:38,000
(Episode 4)

3
00:01:44,958 --> 00:01:46,583
Get ready quick, Bei, let's go!

4
00:01:46,791 --> 00:01:48,458
Do I really gotta come up here for you?

5
00:01:49,416 --> 00:01:50,416
Bro.

6
00:01:50,875 --> 00:01:52,708
The soup's ready in half an hour.

7
00:02:07,375 --> 00:02:08,375
What a shame.

8
00:02:11,833 --> 00:02:12,833
Tonight...

9
00:02:15,416 --> 00:02:16,656
I probably can't have the soup.

10
00:02:26,791 --> 00:02:28,291
Bro, there's someone outside.

11
00:02:40,458 --> 00:02:41,458
Seriously, Bei?

12
00:02:41,875 --> 00:02:43,041
You're not just playing around, are you?

13
00:02:43,041 --> 00:02:44,250
Mind your own business.

14
00:02:46,291 --> 00:02:47,291
Fine.

15
00:02:47,875 --> 00:02:49,035
Anyway, this is for the best.

16
00:02:49,375 --> 00:02:50,375
Safe.

17
00:02:58,875 --> 00:02:59,583
Lüqing.

18
00:02:59,833 --> 00:03:01,833
You've got a great eye for spots!

19
00:03:02,250 --> 00:03:02,916
Look at this place.

20
00:03:03,125 --> 00:03:04,583
Not even a mosquito gets in easily.

21
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:17,240
Finally shook off the tagalong?

22
00:03:17,458 --> 00:03:17,958
Oh dear.
My young master.

23
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,166
Let's talk business first.

24
00:03:22,166 --> 00:03:23,166
Xiaofan.

25
00:03:23,458 --> 00:03:24,500
Bring the documents over.

26
00:03:25,333 --> 00:03:26,458
Yes, on the desk.

27
00:03:26,875 --> 00:03:28,475
The driver's waiting for you downstairs.

28
00:03:41,541 --> 00:03:43,083
This is quite something new.

29
00:03:43,375 --> 00:03:45,125
So, I think...

30
00:03:46,375 --> 00:03:47,458
Hey, Xiaofan's here.

31
00:03:47,916 --> 00:03:49,166
We've been waiting for you.

32
00:03:50,458 --> 00:03:51,458
Sit, sit down.

33
00:03:52,416 --> 00:03:53,166
Alright, alright, alright.

34
00:03:53,291 --> 00:03:54,291
I knew it.

35
00:03:54,958 --> 00:03:55,208
Bro.

36
00:03:55,625 --> 00:03:56,750
Your documents.

37
00:03:58,625 --> 00:03:58,916
I

38
00:03:59,041 --> 00:04:00,708
I also brought some soup.

39
00:04:05,666 --> 00:04:07,106
Take it out and share with everyone.

40
00:04:07,458 --> 00:04:08,458
Okay.

41
00:04:14,916 --> 00:04:15,500
Lüqing.

42
00:04:15,666 --> 00:04:17,506
You just leave documents lying around at home?

43
00:04:17,583 --> 00:04:18,863
Does he really not sneak a peek?

44
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:27,440
That's the good thing about Xiaofan.

45
00:04:27,833 --> 00:04:29,166
Timid and cautious.

46
00:04:29,541 --> 00:04:30,791
He may not be the sharpest,

47
00:04:30,875 --> 00:04:32,250
but he knows his place.

48
00:04:32,750 --> 00:04:33,750
Oh, please.

49
00:04:33,791 --> 00:04:35,208
He doesn't know a damn thing.

50
00:04:35,375 --> 00:04:36,333
You lay it all out for him.

51
00:04:36,333 --> 00:04:37,375
Would he even get it?

52
00:04:45,041 --> 00:04:46,041
Bro.

53
00:04:53,833 --> 00:04:54,833
Ziyang.

54
00:05:14,500 --> 00:05:15,500
Tell me this.

55
00:05:15,708 --> 00:05:17,208
He's got zero trading accounts.

56
00:05:17,458 --> 00:05:19,375
Why bother with financial papers all day?

57
00:05:21,041 --> 00:05:23,541
I'm just browsing.

58
00:05:23,958 --> 00:05:25,583
Don't say that.

59
00:05:25,833 --> 00:05:27,541
Even regular folks enjoy the Global Times.

60
00:05:28,083 --> 00:05:28,583
So what?

61
00:05:28,916 --> 00:05:30,875
So everyone's a UN Secretary-General then?

62
00:05:31,791 --> 00:05:32,791
I think

63
00:05:33,125 --> 00:05:34,250
Lüqing is right.

64
00:05:34,375 --> 00:05:35,208
Xiaofan

65
00:05:35,208 --> 00:05:37,833
just isn't cut out for stock speculation.

66
00:05:38,041 --> 00:05:39,541
What makes Xiaofan so lovely

67
00:05:40,041 --> 00:05:40,958
is his simplicity.

68
00:05:41,041 --> 00:05:42,041
Simplicity.

69
00:05:42,625 --> 00:05:43,625
Stupid and mediocre.

70
00:05:45,625 --> 00:05:46,625
Zhuo Xin.

71
00:05:46,708 --> 00:05:47,875
You got the chills?

72
00:05:50,291 --> 00:05:51,666
No wonder you're so cocky.

73
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:53,708
See?

74
00:05:53,708 --> 00:05:54,976
You just had to make Lüqing speak up.

75
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:55,750
Well?

76
00:05:55,750 --> 00:05:57,041
One word, and you're done for.

77
00:05:57,791 --> 00:05:58,291
Come on, come on.

78
00:05:58,583 --> 00:05:59,583
Let's drink.

79
00:06:00,791 --> 00:06:02,083
That tip from Lüqing

80
00:06:02,125 --> 00:06:04,500
says stock market regulations will be eased.

81
00:06:04,625 --> 00:06:05,625
It's true.

82
00:06:05,916 --> 00:06:06,625
Think about it.

83
00:06:06,791 --> 00:06:09,511
The Songnan and Yunjing factions
are always at each other's throats,

84
00:06:09,791 --> 00:06:11,431
yet they still want to boost the economy.

85
00:06:11,583 --> 00:06:13,703
The only option is to back Songnan to take the reins.

86
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:15,833
The price of rice is going up.

87
00:06:17,125 --> 00:06:18,125
Way up.

88
00:06:19,125 --> 00:06:21,666
Projected to reach one yuan within two years.

89
00:06:22,583 --> 00:06:24,750
Rice is only fifty cents a pound right now.

90
00:06:25,750 --> 00:06:27,458
The state subsidizes rice

91
00:06:27,625 --> 00:06:29,250
to keep prices steady.

92
00:06:29,750 --> 00:06:31,059
They can't keep the prices propped up any longer.

93
00:06:31,083 --> 00:06:32,763
Things are getting shaky down south again,

94
00:06:33,041 --> 00:06:34,750
and there's another official directive from above

95
00:06:34,750 --> 00:06:36,208
to expand rice reserves.

96
00:06:36,750 --> 00:06:39,000
So rice prices are bound to go up.

97
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,083
Rice prices are going up.

98
00:06:42,958 --> 00:06:44,583
Wheat will likely follow suit.

99
00:06:45,833 --> 00:06:46,708
So

100
00:06:46,833 --> 00:06:48,083
once we exit stocks,

101
00:06:48,291 --> 00:06:49,458
we'll be right in time

102
00:06:49,625 --> 00:06:51,465
for this surge in agricultural product prices.

103
00:06:53,916 --> 00:06:56,197
Let's get out of the stock
market first, then we'll talk.

104
00:06:56,833 --> 00:06:57,833
Mm.

105
00:07:06,458 --> 00:07:07,958
You're calling so late. What's up?

106
00:07:07,958 --> 00:07:08,958
Mom.

107
00:07:09,250 --> 00:07:11,750
Did we grow any wheat this year?

108
00:07:11,750 --> 00:07:12,666
You silly boy.

109
00:07:12,666 --> 00:07:13,750
Calling in the middle of the night,

110
00:07:13,750 --> 00:07:15,125
just to ask if we grew wheat.

111
00:07:15,500 --> 00:07:16,875
What wheat?

112
00:07:17,041 --> 00:07:17,791
Growing wheat now,

113
00:07:17,791 --> 00:07:19,250
you lose dozens of yuan per mu.

114
00:07:19,333 --> 00:07:20,333
Who still plants wheat?

115
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:22,180
Nobody in the village grows wheat anymore.

116
00:07:22,541 --> 00:07:23,958
Not even to feed our own family?

117
00:07:23,958 --> 00:07:25,833
We used to when you were still home,

118
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,375
but your dad's gotten picky.

119
00:07:27,375 --> 00:07:28,541
He likes Huanglong wheat now.

120
00:07:28,625 --> 00:07:30,375
So we simply plowed up all our wheat.

121
00:07:30,375 --> 00:07:30,833
Mom.
We'll put in apple trees this year.

122
00:07:31,750 --> 00:07:33,833
How can you not even grow food for yourselves?

123
00:07:34,916 --> 00:07:36,396
What if you can't get wheat later on?

124
00:07:36,708 --> 00:07:37,875
That'll land you in big trouble.

125
00:07:37,875 --> 00:07:39,115
There's no way we can't get it.

126
00:07:39,541 --> 00:07:40,976
It's sold everywhere in the village now.

127
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,226
No more trips to the county seat.

128
00:07:42,250 --> 00:07:44,570
We go through
four to five hundred jin of wheat each year!

129
00:07:44,916 --> 00:07:46,708
Suppose it hits one yuan per jin next year,

130
00:07:47,458 --> 00:07:49,541
then all your work is in vain.

131
00:07:49,625 --> 00:07:50,666
One yuan a jin?

132
00:07:50,875 --> 00:07:51,500
Xiaofan.

133
00:07:51,500 --> 00:07:52,620
You're not serious, are you?

134
00:07:52,750 --> 00:07:53,208
Huh?

135
00:07:53,333 --> 00:07:54,916
You heard something, didn't you?

136
00:07:55,166 --> 00:07:56,458
People will starve!

137
00:07:56,500 --> 00:07:57,000
Oh dear.
Xiaofan says

138
00:07:57,458 --> 00:07:58,750
wheat prices are going up.

139
00:07:59,541 --> 00:08:00,041
What are we gonna do?

140
00:08:00,041 --> 00:08:01,500
No, no, no.

141
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:02,541
I said "if."

142
00:08:04,750 --> 00:08:06,333
I'm hanging up now.

143
00:08:15,208 --> 00:08:16,208
Bro.

144
00:08:16,750 --> 00:08:17,750
Are you hungry?

145
00:08:17,958 --> 00:08:19,318
Let me fix you a late-night snack.

146
00:08:22,375 --> 00:08:23,416
Do you know

147
00:08:23,750 --> 00:08:25,291
what's the most valuable thing?

148
00:08:28,875 --> 00:08:29,875
Bro.

149
00:08:30,250 --> 00:08:31,833
Information is worth the most.

150
00:08:34,541 --> 00:08:35,291
I'm sorry.

151
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:36,500
Bro.

152
00:08:36,708 --> 00:08:39,125
Did I mess things up?

153
00:08:39,583 --> 00:08:40,863
What could you possibly mess up?

154
00:08:41,916 --> 00:08:42,916
I brought you along

155
00:08:43,541 --> 00:08:44,458
to show you

156
00:08:44,458 --> 00:08:45,833
how business really works.

157
00:08:51,250 --> 00:08:54,000
You passed that news back to the village.

158
00:08:54,708 --> 00:08:55,948
What difference does that make?

159
00:08:56,791 --> 00:08:58,125
A few hundred yuan in crops.

160
00:08:59,583 --> 00:09:01,333
Do you know how much money

161
00:09:01,333 --> 00:09:02,875
you could have earned with that news?

162
00:09:03,875 --> 00:09:05,291
Can't you aim higher?

163
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:09,583
If you're at least salvageable,

164
00:09:10,375 --> 00:09:12,055
don't bring shame on me starting tomorrow.

165
00:09:16,458 --> 00:09:17,458
No.

166
00:09:17,500 --> 00:09:18,583
Can't you two be apart for even a second?

167
00:09:18,583 --> 00:09:19,583
Hey, hey, hey.

168
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:21,041
Let's get back to business.

169
00:09:22,041 --> 00:09:23,083
I've run the numbers.

170
00:09:23,291 --> 00:09:25,666
Missing this trend means heavy losses.

171
00:09:25,833 --> 00:09:27,267
I squeezed two hundred thousand yuan

172
00:09:27,291 --> 00:09:28,291
out of my old man.

173
00:09:28,541 --> 00:09:30,416
I got the same amount too.

174
00:09:32,375 --> 00:09:33,375
Just say it.

175
00:09:33,666 --> 00:09:34,666
How much more is missing?

176
00:09:35,916 --> 00:09:36,541
Actually
it's not that much more.

177
00:09:37,583 --> 00:09:38,583
Just...

178
00:09:38,916 --> 00:09:39,916
Hang on.

179
00:09:43,166 --> 00:09:45,041
Fanfan! Xiaofan! Hurry!

180
00:09:45,458 --> 00:09:46,698
Something happened to your dad!

181
00:09:46,916 --> 00:09:47,916
Xiaofan.

182
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:48,291
Yeah?

183
00:09:48,625 --> 00:09:49,666
Your mom's on the phone.

184
00:09:56,583 --> 00:09:58,291
Why did she call here?

185
00:09:58,291 --> 00:09:58,875
Xiaofan.
Mom.

186
00:09:59,625 --> 00:10:00,083
What happened?

187
00:10:00,083 --> 00:10:01,708
Big trouble ahead.

188
00:10:02,208 --> 00:10:04,166
The news sent your dad into a panic.

189
00:10:04,416 --> 00:10:05,916
He borrowed the village chief's tricycle

190
00:10:05,916 --> 00:10:07,309
and rushed to town to buy up wheat.

191
00:10:07,333 --> 00:10:09,000
But he got hit by a car along the way.

192
00:10:09,291 --> 00:10:10,291
Is Dad okay?

193
00:10:10,375 --> 00:10:11,750
Your dad's in the hospital now.

194
00:10:11,833 --> 00:10:13,166
The police even blamed us.

195
00:10:13,750 --> 00:10:14,833
Send money back quickly!

196
00:10:15,041 --> 00:10:15,458
Hurry!
Okay, okay, okay.

197
00:10:16,375 --> 00:10:16,791
Mom.
Don't panic.

198
00:10:18,083 --> 00:10:19,123
I'll head back right away.

199
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:27,500
Bro.

200
00:10:29,958 --> 00:10:31,166
I need to go back home.

201
00:10:31,375 --> 00:10:32,375
Talk outside.

202
00:10:38,416 --> 00:10:39,291
Tell Manager Li

203
00:10:39,333 --> 00:10:40,559
to get me five thousand in cash.

204
00:10:40,583 --> 00:10:41,726
Deduct it from this private room's bill.

205
00:10:41,750 --> 00:10:42,750
Got it.

206
00:10:49,875 --> 00:10:50,875
I'm sorry, bro.

207
00:10:51,333 --> 00:10:52,916
I'm still causing you trouble.

208
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:01,000
Go on.

209
00:11:01,083 --> 00:11:02,163
Give my regards to Mrs. Lu.

210
00:11:07,125 --> 00:11:08,125
Thank you, bro.

211
00:11:08,416 --> 00:11:09,416
Thank you, bro.

212
00:11:13,208 --> 00:11:14,208
Bro.

213
00:11:14,541 --> 00:11:15,541
Will you be home tonight?

214
00:11:15,916 --> 00:11:16,916
I'll make soup for you.

215
00:11:19,291 --> 00:11:19,875
No need.

216
00:11:20,208 --> 00:11:21,267
Soup doesn't appeal to me lately.

217
00:11:21,291 --> 00:11:22,666
I'll cook you some congee, okay?

218
00:11:34,583 --> 00:11:35,583
So you see,

219
00:11:35,666 --> 00:11:37,208
background sets your vision,

220
00:11:37,416 --> 00:11:38,750
and vision sets your choices.

221
00:11:39,208 --> 00:11:40,791
Alright, Master Zhuo.

222
00:11:41,333 --> 00:11:42,666
When Lüqing gets back soon

223
00:11:42,666 --> 00:11:43,666
and sees you like this,

224
00:11:43,666 --> 00:11:44,786
do you think he'll be happy?

225
00:11:46,625 --> 00:11:49,333
Liking men isn't some minor illness.

226
00:11:49,375 --> 00:11:51,083
You can't just take medicine to cure it.

227
00:11:51,541 --> 00:11:54,250
Even if you run Lu Xiaofan off,

228
00:11:54,500 --> 00:11:55,791
the truth remains unchanged.

229
00:11:56,416 --> 00:11:57,791
Vermilion gates match stone lions,

230
00:11:58,083 --> 00:11:59,416
wooden doors match bamboo horses.

231
00:12:00,125 --> 00:12:02,000
Lu Xiaofan is just a country bumpkin.

232
00:12:02,500 --> 00:12:03,791
Would you have Lüqing

233
00:12:03,791 --> 00:12:05,958
tangled up with him over petty,

234
00:12:06,250 --> 00:12:07,708
small-town trivialities?

235
00:12:08,875 --> 00:12:10,500
Bei Lüqing does like men.

236
00:12:10,625 --> 00:12:12,083
But he deserves better.

237
00:12:12,416 --> 00:12:13,416
Fine, fine, fine.

238
00:12:18,500 --> 00:12:19,958
Hello, Fanfan.

239
00:12:20,250 --> 00:12:21,250
You alright over there?

240
00:12:21,500 --> 00:12:22,500
Oh.

241
00:12:22,833 --> 00:12:23,583
Listen,

242
00:12:23,833 --> 00:12:25,333
Lu Qing reached out

243
00:12:25,333 --> 00:12:26,351
to the best hospital nearby.

244
00:12:26,375 --> 00:12:27,695
Your dad got admitted right away.

245
00:12:28,083 --> 00:12:29,458
He even set us both up

246
00:12:29,458 --> 00:12:31,083
for complete physical exams.

247
00:12:31,625 --> 00:12:32,250
Ah.

248
00:12:32,458 --> 00:12:34,541
All's well over here, really.

249
00:12:34,916 --> 00:12:36,583
Take good care of yourself.

250
00:12:36,833 --> 00:12:37,833
Oh, and,

251
00:12:37,958 --> 00:12:40,833
make sure you thank Lu Qing for us.

252
00:12:43,375 --> 00:12:44,458
I heard

253
00:12:44,750 --> 00:12:46,458
Lu Xin's mom's heading back home.

254
00:12:57,166 --> 00:12:58,166
Come on.

255
00:12:58,875 --> 00:13:00,583
Congrats to Lüqing

256
00:13:00,916 --> 00:13:02,166
on graduating successfully.

257
00:13:08,166 --> 00:13:08,958
Lüqing.

258
00:13:09,166 --> 00:13:10,846
Are you really not going to keep studying?

259
00:13:17,125 --> 00:13:18,250
I've thought it through.

260
00:13:18,666 --> 00:13:19,666
I think it's better

261
00:13:19,708 --> 00:13:21,208
to go out and work earlier instead.

262
00:13:23,833 --> 00:13:25,958
The market has just started to thrive.

263
00:13:26,625 --> 00:13:28,333
More studies mean nothing.

264
00:13:29,125 --> 00:13:29,791
In the end,

265
00:13:29,791 --> 00:13:32,250
it's just about landing a small official title.

266
00:13:35,083 --> 00:13:36,083
Son.

267
00:13:36,416 --> 00:13:38,583
Here's your startup money.

268
00:13:39,125 --> 00:13:40,405
Go out there and make your mark.

269
00:13:40,833 --> 00:13:41,791
Lüqing will report

270
00:13:41,791 --> 00:13:43,517
to the Ministry of Foreign Affairs next week.

271
00:13:43,541 --> 00:13:45,583
Money from unknown sources is not safe.

272
00:13:46,333 --> 00:13:48,041
Unknown sources?

273
00:13:48,833 --> 00:13:50,208
A mother's money for her son.

274
00:13:50,208 --> 00:13:51,958
How is that unclear in origin?

275
00:13:53,416 --> 00:13:55,833
Or is Mr. Bei implying something?

276
00:14:03,750 --> 00:14:04,750
Xiaofan.

277
00:14:05,083 --> 00:14:06,226
Now that Lüqing has graduated,

278
00:14:06,250 --> 00:14:07,250
why don't you

279
00:14:08,041 --> 00:14:09,161
stop living in the dorm too,

280
00:14:09,458 --> 00:14:10,625
and come back home to live?

281
00:14:11,416 --> 00:14:12,601
He moved out of the dorm long ago.

282
00:14:12,625 --> 00:14:13,625
Huh?

283
00:14:14,791 --> 00:14:15,791
Xiaofan.

284
00:14:15,875 --> 00:14:17,333
You're not living on campus?

285
00:14:22,708 --> 00:14:24,708
